      <h1>Welcome to Headius!</h1>
      <p>Thanks for finding us. Here's what we do and why it matters.</p>
    </hgroup>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="highlight">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div>
        <pre><code class="highlight"><span class="c"># == Headius::Mission</span>
<span class="c"># Supporting JRuby. Funding its future.</span></code></pre>
        <h2>What We Do</h2>
        <p>
          Headius Enterprises provides support and services to users of JRuby and related technologies. Through this work, we've become the primary funding source for the JRuby project and its ongoing development.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your partnership with Headius Enterprises ensures the future of JRuby and supports the ongoing development of the open source JRuby ecosystem.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <pre><code class="highlight"><span class="c"># == Headius::Origin</span>
<span class="c"># The name goes back to 1992.</span></code></pre>
        <h2>Why "Headius"?</h2>
        <p>
          The Headius name has been associated with Chief Architect Charles Oliver Nutter since 1992, carrying with it three decades of open source management and contribution. Our commitment to the Free and Open Source Software community is at the core of everything we do.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="container">
    <pre><code class="highlight"><span class="c"># == Headius::Partnership</span>
<span class="c"># A win-win model.</span></code></pre>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>
      JRuby development is funded through support subscriptions and contracts with Headius Enterprises. It's a win-win partnership: your applications receive ongoing support from the people who actually build JRuby, while JRuby continues to thrive as an open source project.
    </p>
    <p>
      Choose the level of support that fits your team — or <a href="<%= relative_url '/contact' %>">get in touch</a> if you need something custom.
    </p>
